The paper deals with semantic segmentation of medical images using deep learning, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of adversarial networks for training is also a key aspect of the paper, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper specifically focuses on the detection of aggressive prostate cancer, which is a medical imaging application (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges of working with small datasets, which is a common problem in neural network training and falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE).
